Q1. Write a Python program to shuffle a deck of card. Display the cards obtained by a user in 5 attempts.  


import random
suits = ['Hearts', 'Diamonds', 'Clubs', 'Spades']
ranks = ['2', '3', '4', '5', '6', '7', '8', '9', '10',
         'Jack', 'Queen', 'King', 'Ace']
deck = [(rank, suit) for suit in suits for rank in ranks]
random.shuffle(deck)
print("Cards drawn:")
for i in range(5):
    print(deck[i][0], "of", deck[i][1])


